<instructionsection id="FAMIN_advsimd" title="FAMIN -- A64" type="instruction">
  <docvars>
    <docvar key="advsimd-reguse" value="3reg-same" />
    <docvar key="advsimd-type" value="simd" />
    <docvar key="instr-class" value="advsimd" />
    <docvar key="isa" value="A64" />
    <docvar key="mnemonic" value="FAMIN" />
  </docvars>
  <heading>FAMIN</heading>
  <desc>
    <brief>
      <para>Floating-point absolute minimum</para>
    </brief>
    <authored>
      <para>Floating-point absolute minimum. This instruction determines the minimum absolute value from floating-point elements of the first source vector and the corresponding floating-point elements of the second source vector, and places the results in the corresponding elements of the destination vector.</para>
      <para>The behavior is as follows:</para>
      <list type="unordered">
        <listitem><content>When <xref linkend="AArch64.fpcr">FPCR</xref>.DN is 0, if either element is a NaN, the result is a quiet NaN.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>When <xref linkend="AArch64.fpcr">FPCR</xref>.DN is 1, if either element is a NaN, the result is the Default NaN.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>Denormalized inputs and results are never flushed to zero, as if <xref linkend="AArch64.fpcr">FPCR</xref>.{FZ, FZ16, FIZ} is {0, 0, 0}.</content></listitem>
        <listitem><content>Denormalized inputs never generate an Input Denormal floating-point exception.</content></listitem>
      </list>
    </authored>
  </desc>
  <alias_list howmany="0"></alias_list>
